Number = {5-6},
Pages = {262-269},
Abstract = {The pollination pattern in a Scots pine (Pinus sylvestris L.) seed
   orchard consisting of 28 clones was studied using nine microsatellite
   (SSR) loci. The nine SSR loci produced unique multilocus genotypes for
   each of the orchard's 28 clones and allowed paternal assignment of the
   studied 305 seed using paternity exclusion probability of 99.9\%. Fifty
   two percent of the studied seeds were sired by outside the orchard
   pollen sources (i.e., pollen contamination) and as expected, low selfing
   (2.3\%) was detected. These results are valuable for the evaluation of
   the seed orchard function and the impact of contamination on the
   expected genetic gain.},
